  "chapter": {
    "number": 49,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Evanescence of Wealth"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "For the choirmaster. A Psalm of the sons of Korah."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear this, all you peoples;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "listen, all inhabitants of the world,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "both low and high,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rich and poor alike.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "My mouth will impart wisdom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the meditation of my heart will bring understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will incline my ear to a proverb;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will express my riddle with the harp:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why should I fear in times of trouble,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when wicked usurpers surround me?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They trust in their wealth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and boast in their great riches.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "No man can possibly redeem his brother",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4383
          },
          {
            "text": "or pay his ransom to God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the redemption of his soul is costly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and never can payment suffice,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "that he should live on forever",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and not see decay.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For it is clear that wise men die,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the foolish and the senseless both perish",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and leave their wealth to others.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Their graves",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4384
          },
          {
            "text": "are their eternal homes—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their dwellings for endless generations—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even though their lands were their namesakes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But a man, despite his wealth, cannot endure;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he is like the beasts that perish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is the fate of the self-confident",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4385
          },
          {
            "text": "and their followers who endorse their sayings.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Like sheep they are destined for Sheol.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Death will be their shepherd.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The upright will rule them in the morning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their form will decay in Sheol,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "far from their lofty abode.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But God will redeem my life from Sheol,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for He will surely take me to Himself.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "Selah"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not be amazed when a man grows rich,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the splendor of his house increases.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For when he dies, he will carry nothing away;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his abundance will not follow him down.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though in his lifetime he blesses his soul—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and men praise you when you prosper—",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "he will join the generation of his fathers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who will never see the light of day.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A man who has riches without understanding",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is like the beasts that perish.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
